com.kallasoft.smugmug.api.json.entity
Class Category

java.lang.Object
  com.kallasoft.smugmug.api.json.entity.Category

public class Category
extends Object

Class used to define a category (or subcategory) and the subcategories and albums it contains.

In some cases when the instance represents a subcategory, there will be a value present for parentCategoryID, otherwise in most cases that value will be null.

Author:
Riyad Kalla

Category

public Category(org.json.JSONObject categoryObject)
         throws IllegalArgumentException,
                org.json.JSONException
Construct a new category or subcategory by safely parsing all known values out of the given JSONObject.

If a property is not available from the JSONObject, it's value is simply set to null and ignored and parsing continues.

Parameters:
categoryObject - The JSONObject that will be queried for all the known properties for this category or subcategory.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if categoryObject is null.
org.json.JSONException - if any JSONObject-related exception occurs.

Parameters:
id - The ID of the category or subcategory.

parentCategoryID - The ID of the parent category to this subcategory.
albumList - The list of Album that belong to this category or subcategory, if any.
subCategoryList - A list of Category that represent the subcategories of the given category, if any.
